  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-23 19:43 UTC \u2014 [P1: Copy Intelligence] Define When the Recent-10 Window Should Actually Turn On So the Overnight Retrospective Doesn\u2019t Pretend Sparse History Is Rich Enough for Short-Term vs Long-Term Comparison\n\n**Task:** Choose the minimum ledger depth required before the recent-10 windowed comparison should activate, so the first windowed lens turns on only when it is truly more informative than redundant.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Decision: require at least **20 runs per profile** before activating recent-10.\n- Why:\n  - creates a meaningful full-history baseline\n  - prevents the recent window from overlapping too much with total history too early\n  - keeps recent-10 as a real short-term lens rather than sparse-history theater\n- Wrote activation-threshold artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v12v-recent10-activation-threshold.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis threshold feels right. I don\u2019t want the system claiming to compare short-term versus long-term behavior when \u201clong-term\u201d is only a handful of points. Twenty runs is enough to make the split feel honest without waiting forever.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep recent-10 dormant until a profile reaches 20 runs.\n- Activate recent-10 vs full-history comparison only at that threshold or higher.\n\n**Next:** On the next P1 heartbeat, define how the retrospective script should expose dormant-vs-active window status so the report stays explicit about when the recent-10 lens is not yet meaningful.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-23 19:33 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Define the First Recent-Window Filter for the Overnight Ledger So the Next Retrospective Layer Is Ready When History Depth Finally Makes Windowed Comparison Worth It\n\n**Task:** Choose the first recent-window filter the overnight retrospective should use once the history ledger has enough runs to support a meaningful short-term vs long-term comparison.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Recommended first recent-window filter:\n  - **most recent 10 runs per profile**\n- Why this is the right first window:\n  - large enough to show short-term drift\n  - small enough to stay sensitive to recent change\n  - simple and intuitive for the first windowed comparison\n- Wrote window-filter artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v12u-first-recent-window-filter.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is a good future-ready choice. I don\u2019t want to build the window logic too early, but I do want the design call settled so the next step is obvious once the ledger has more than a trivial amount of history.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Use recent-10 as the first windowed lens when the ledger is deep enough.\n- Compare recent-10 against full-history summary rather than inventing a more complex window stack too soon.\n\n**Next:** On the next P4 heartbeat, define the minimum history depth required before the recent-10 filter should become active instead of staying dormant.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-23 19:13 UT",
